 :tx/rationale "THRESHOLD AUTO-CALIBRATION: After each harvest, compute the optimal concept join threshold from the observed cosine distribution. Algorithm: (1) Collect all cosine similarities between observations and their nearest concept (from :exploration/concept Refs + concept embeddings). (2) Compute the bimodal split point — the value that maximizes the gap between 'clearly in' and 'clearly out' observations. This is Otsu's method applied to cosine similarities: find threshold T that minimizes intra-class variance of the two groups (above-T and below-T). (3) Store the computed threshold as :policy/concept-join-threshold datom. (4) Next observation uses this calibrated threshold. Bootstrap: first 5 observations use the embedder default (0.20 for model2vec, 0.65 for hash). After 5+ observations, Otsu takes over. The harvest.rs optimal_threshold function already implements exactly this pattern for crystallization scoring — same math, different input distribution. Convergence property: as the store accumulates observations, the threshold converges to the natural boundary of the embedding space for THIS project's domain. A Go CLI project and a React project will converge to different thresholds because their observation-concept similarity distributions differ. This is C9 compliance: the parameter becomes project-specific without manual tuning. Traces to: ADR-FOUNDATION-031, C9, OBSERVER-4, INV-EMBEDDING-004."
